The paper deals with multi-agent navigation, which is a problem in the field of multi-agent systems (MAS). Therefore, cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes an approach that allows agents to compute time-efficient and collision-free motions, which involves decision-making and optimization, indicating that it could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The problem of multi-agent navigation also involves robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) likely categories. Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to optimize the set of velocities for navigation tasks, which could place it under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
